Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Beat eggs, milk and sour cream in large bowl with wire whisk until well blended. Add broccoli, dry stuffing mix, ham and 1/2 cup of the cheese; mix lightly. Pour mixture into 2-qt. baking dish or 9-inch pie plate; cover loosely with foil. Bake 1 hour. Uncover; sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 5 min. or until cheese is melted and mixture is cooked through.